&lt;p&gt;Thoughtworks is a global technology consultancy that integrates strategy, design and engineering to drive digital innovation. We are expanding our ANZ Public Sector, Healthcare and Life Sciences practice to meet a step-change in demand across federal, state and territory governments, with a particular focus on Queensland and the Commonwealth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are hiring a Client Partner to lead a portfolio of strategic public sector accounts, with healthcare and life sciences as a secondary focus. This is a senior, market-facing role for someone who already operates with credibility at SES and C-suite level in Australian government and who understands how to convert relationships into multi-year, outcome-based engagements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why this role, why now&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Queensland Government has allocated $1B to the Minister for Customer Services for a whole-of-government technology refresh. Olympics infrastructure investment is accelerating modernisation across transport, health and citizen services. At the Commonwealth level, the DTA Investment Oversight Framework continues to drive consolidation and reform across major digital projects. Thoughtworks is positioned to lead in legacy modernisation, AI delivery, data platforms and digital service transformation. This role exists to convert that positioning into sustained portfolio growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we offer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A flat, transparent culture that values judgement and ownership. Direct access to global capability across AI, data, modernisation and digital transformation, including the AI/works platform. A leadership team that backs its people and expects them to back themselves. A practice with real momentum and a clear plan for the next three years.&lt;/p&gt;
